name: Bobby's Shack

reviews.review_text:
While the view is nice, beach facing and pretty scenes, the rudeness of the service staff is applaudable. We were served extremely cold soup and when we pointed it out, he made a dirty face and said "it is so hot". Also after taking our order of breads after 30 minutes he returns saying we don't have that particular bread.

The food is also average at best. The xacuti didn't feel unique at all and lacked flavour overall.

Avoid.

Dis shack is located at candolim beach in goa its 45 mins drive from mapusa taxi stand one of the pleasant and less crowded beach of goa if u ask abt ambience than its really cool and beautiful not very noisy and staff is very friendly and co operative one more thing they dont serve pork or beef so we selected this place for dinner ..we ordered chicken white cheese pasta it was the best white sauce pasta i had in time full of chicken and cream with olives but little oily so i asled dem to prepare it in less oil and to the point it was yummiest if u r white pasta sauce lover than this place is for u i ordered chicken steak it was ok ok in taste not great was sweet in taste i asked them to prepare little spicy so on request they did but not great yes i requested to put more vegetables and they acknowledged that was really good gesture of staff i really loved the place u can try on ur trip to goa they wont disappoint u little expensive

We have been coming to Goa for 15 years and always used Bobby's shack.  The food is excellent the staff are ALL attentive and very friendly.   Definitely the best shack in Goa.  You must visit this shack. Well done Sanjay Kash and all the hard working staff that have continued to maintain an excellent reputation in memory of dear Bobby godbless
Jack and Bridgette

description:
**Bobby's Shack: A Goan Gem by the Beach**

Nestled in the serene atmosphere of Candolim Beach, Bobby's Shack has amassed a commendable rating of 4.1 from a collective of 753 reviews. Known for its laid-back charm and beachside setting, it garners acclaim for attributes like "beautiful beach views" and "friendly music-focused environment," with the tags beach (69), shacks (24), music (15), and beer (11) echoing through customer feedback.

**Ambiance & Design**

Walking into Bobby's Shack, guests are greeted by an inviting and unpretentious beach shack ambiance. The rustic décor, characterized by wooden seating and vibrant beach-themed decor, exemplifies the quintessential Goan coastal experience. The photos reveal a picturesque setting, where sun-kissed sands meet the azure waves, creating a perfect backdrop for a relaxed meal. Reviews frequently mention the pleasant and not overly noisy atmosphere, accentuated by gentle waves and soft music, which enhances the tranquil dining experience.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The menu at Bobby's Shack is varied, catering to a range of palates, though it notably excludes pork and beef. Highlights include the much-praised chicken white cheese pasta, which one reviewer lovingly described as "the best white sauce pasta I've had in a while," bursting with chicken, cream, and olives—albeit slightly oily. The xacuti curry, however, has garnered mixed feelings, described by some as lacking the necessary depth of flavor. Presentation is simple yet appealing, encapsulating the shack's easygoing spirit. While vegetarian and chicken options are available, seafood also makes a notable appearance; however, the reviews suggest there could be more attention to flavor and uniqueness across the dishes.

**Customer Experience & Service**

Customer service at Bobby's Shack appears to be a hit or miss, as reflected in the reviews. While some diners laud the attentiveness and friendliness of the staff, others have reported instances of rudeness that detracted from their experience. One frequent visitor emphasized the staff's dedication, reflecting on positive interactions throughout many visits over the years. It’s worth noting that reviews indicate a responsive kitchen, willing to accommodate dietary requests, and while prices may be on the higher side for the area, the overall experience seems to provide good value for many.

**Popularity & Reviews**

The buzz surrounding Bobby's Shack is palpable, with many reviewers highlighting it as a must-visit for anyone traveling to Goa. Among the steady stream of praises for its ambiance and standout dishes, there are cautionary tales regarding consistency in service and meal preparation. The restaurant holds a reputation in the community, with long-standing patrons reaffirming their loyalty over the years.

**Utilizing Visual Content**

The charm of Bobby's Shack is beautifully depicted in the customer-provided photos. One image showcases diners enjoying meals against a breathtaking sunset backdrop, illustrating the shacks' close proximity to the beach and the picturesque scenery that enhances any dining experience. Another visual capture of the vibrant feast highlights the simplicity of presentation, while a third photograph reveals the cozy communal seating arrangement that fosters a welcoming environment.

In summary, Bobby's Shack encapsulates the laid-back spirit of a beach getaway, offering captivating views, flavorful dishes, and a vibrant atmosphere. Though service consistency may vary, the warm ambience and culinary highlights—from creamy pastas to lively beachside gatherings—continue to draw visitors back for more memorable meals. As you plan your trip to Goa, a stop at Bobby's Shack should undoubtedly be on your itinerary.
